{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"1538cb73-00e5-4c16-9923-e2676d645b50","content":"Yes — C# fully supports `stackalloc`'d `Span<nint>` and `Span<nuint>`. Both compiled and ran without issues:\n\n```\nnint[0] = 42, nint[1] = 9223372036854775807, length = 4\nnuint[0] = 99, nuint[1] = 18446744073709551615, length = 3\n```\n\n`nint`/`nuint` are unmanaged types (required by `stackalloc`), so this works out of the box. On this 64-bit system, `nint.MaxValue` is `long.MaxValue` and `nuint.MaxValue` is `ulong.MaxValue`.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"63f0f68c-e61e-4ffb-805c-1b6f615ab45e","outputTokens":172,"requestId":"5C4F:199131:1022E95:140E2BB:69FFD747"},"id":"a16bc8c0-607d-4cb3-b076-258303070ed3","timestamp":"2026-05-10T00:54:36.137Z","parentId":"46d57db2-8c8b-4bc1-8fc0-b42b338a022e"}
